name: RecordData
description: The RecordData class describes or references log or audit data from a given type of tool and provides a means to annotate the output.

DateTime.name: DateTime
DateTime.description: A timestamp of the data found in the RecordItem or URL classes.

Description.name: Description
Description.description: A free-form text description of the data provided in the RecordItem or URL classes.

Application.name: Application
Application.description: Identifies the tool used to generate the data in the RecordItem or URL classes.

RecordPattern.name: RecordPattern
RecordPattern.description: A search string to precisely find the relevant data in the RecordItem or URL classes.  See Section 3.22.2.

RecordItem.name: RecordItem
RecordItem.description: Log, audit, or forensic data to support the conclusions made during the course of analyzing the incident.

URL.name: URL
URL.description: A URL reference to a log or audit data.

FileData.name: FileData
FileData.description: The files involved in the incident.  See Section 3.25.

WindowsRegistryKeysModified.name: WindowsRegistryKeysModified
WindowsRegistryKeysModified.description: The registry keys that were involved in the incident.  See Section 3.23.

CertificateData.name: CertificateData
CertificateData.description: The certificates that were involved in the incident.  See Section 3.24.

AdditionalData.name: AdditionalData
AdditionalData.description: An extension mechanism for data not explicitly represented in the data model.

ext-restriction.name: ext-restriction
ext-restriction.description: A means by which to extend the restriction attribute.  See Section 5.1.1.
